                  <msItem>
                     <p> SACOMBE. <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> de <surname>Holt</surname>
                        </persName> 
                  and <persName nymRef="Holt">
                           <forename>Alice</forename> his wife</persName> attorn and 
                  in their places appoint 
                  <persName>
                           <forename>Robert</forename> 
                           <surname>Bray</surname>
                        </persName> to receive
                  seisin of the manor of <placeName type="manor" key="place_1083648">Sanecompe</placeName>, with the advowson
                  of the church, which were Elizabeth's, the wife of <persName>
                           <forename>Roger</forename> de <surname>Elmerugge</surname>
                        </persName>, in <placeName key="place_1083551">Staundon</placeName> and
                  <placeName key="place_1083385">Epcomp</placeName>. 
                  Dated at <placeName role="date" key="place_107054">Northampton</placeName> the Monday next after the feast
                  of the Annunciation B.V.M.. <origDate notBefore="1376-01-25" notAfter="1377-01-24">50 Ed. III</origDate>. 
                   </p>
